cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the problem of content identification with lossy recovery, which involves information theory, multimedia processing, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the biometrical identification problem and the content identification problem, which are related to computer vision and machine learning, respectively. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are also likely categories. The paper also involves cryptography and security, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as another possible category. Finally, the paper uses the information spectrum method and strong converse techniques, which are related to statistical learning theory and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category.
